Mongodb query find if documents exist in the DB

I've been trying to do something I don't know if I can in MongoDB (or any other DB), but what I want is to do a find type of query where the return is individual to each of the attributes. It's like a "Find which ones exist".

For example, I'd like to send something like:

db.getCollection('products').find({'id': {$or: [1,2,3,4,5] } })

And I'd like the answer to be something like:

{
  1: true,
  2: true,
  3: false,
  4: false,
  5: true
}

Is there a way to do so? I'm thinking not, but I'd like to know if there is anything I can do to make it work to avoid extra processing on my server side.

embedfield:
Debezium Connect doesnt provide 'before' field after updating an item

I set up a topic for kafka which emits the data changes which comes from debezium. My db is mongo which is created from mongo:6 docker image. kafka is created from confluentinc/cp-kafka:latest, debezium is from debezium/connect:2.4, and zookeeper from confluentinc/cp-zookeeper:latest

Im trying to get the before and after states of the data after update or delete operation to log them. This is my configuration for topic creation:

{
"name": "management-workspaces-deneme",
"config": {
    "connector.class": "io.debezium.connector.mongodb.MongoDbConnector",
    "mongodb.connection.string": "mongodb://192.168.2.15:27030",
    "topic.prefix": "eys",
    "capture.mode":"change_streams_with_pre_image",
    "mongodb.poll.interval.ms": "5000",
    "database.history.kafka.bootstrap.servers": "172.23.0.3:29092",
    "heartbeat.interval.ms": "5000",
    "database.include.list":"wins",
    "collection.include.list": "wins.workspaces,wins.tasks"
}

In debezium's docs, it says ;

The value of a change event for an update in the sample customers collection has the same schema as a create event for that collection. Likewise, the event value’s payload has the same structure. However, the event value payload contains different values in an update event. An update event includes an after value only if the capture.mode option is set to change_streams_update_full. A before value is provided if the capture.mode option is set to one of the *_with_pre_image option.

As you can see I added this setting to config. But it doesnt work. I can consume the change and see the message like this

"payload":{"before":null,"after":null,"updateDescription":{"removedFields":null,"updatedFields":"{\\"description\\": \\"666teste\\"}",

but its before and after field is coming null. How can I see these fields? Any help is much appreciated.
answer: So in both of your entities must be a field of the other entity and specify their relationship with annotations. In one of them you have to tell on which column you want to join and in the other you have to set the field name referring to that entity in the other entity.

embedfield:
MongoDB Realm Sync session automatically disconnects after connecting

I am trying to connect to my Mongo DB collection as an app user, with flexible sync. But the sync connection disconnects automatically after a few seconds it seems. Here's my code.

class Person extends Realm.Object {
  static schema = dummyCollectionSchema;
}
class PersonInfo extends Realm.Object {
  static schema = dummyCollection_infoSchema;
}

async function connect() {
  const app = new Realm.App({ id: "application", timeout: 10000 });
  const credentials = Realm.Credentials.emailPassword("usr", "pwd");
  const user = await app.logIn(credentials);

  const config = {
    schema: [Person, PersonInfo],
    sync: {
      user,
      flexible: true,
      initialSubscriptions: {
        update: (subs, realm) => {
          subs.add(realm.objects(Person), { name: "Persons" });
        },
      },
    },
  };
  return await Realm.open(config);
}

async function run() {
  const realm = await connect();

  console.log(`>>> Connected: ${realm.syncSession.isConnected()}`);
  // If I write a document to my collection here, it gets synced to Atlas

  // wait 10 seconds
  await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 10000));  
  console.log(`>>> Connected: ${realm.syncSession.isConnected()}`);
  // If I write a document  here, it does not appear in Atlas. It appears the next time I run the script though.
}

run().catch(err => console.error(`${err}`));

I do not get any errors (neither in the code, nor in the realm logs), but the second console.log says Connected: false. If I write to the database, it always writes to the local realm. But anything that is written after a few seconds of connection does not get synced (gets synced the next time I run my code). What am I doing wrong here?

Embed Field: MongoDB Realm Sync session automatically disconnects after connecting

I am trying to connect to my Mongo DB collection as an app user, with flexible sync. But the sync connection disconnects automatically after a few seconds it seems. Here's my code.

class Person extends Realm.Object {
  static schema = dummyCollectionSchema;
}
class PersonInfo extends Realm.Object {
  static schema = dummyCollection_infoSchema;
}

async function connect() {
  const app = new Realm.App({ id: "application", timeout: 10000 });
  const credentials = Realm.Credentials.emailPassword("usr", "pwd");
  const user = await app.logIn(credentials);

  const config = {
    schema: [Person, PersonInfo],
    sync: {
      user,
      flexible: true,
      initialSubscriptions: {
        update: (subs, realm) => {
          subs.add(realm.objects(Person), { name: "Persons" });
        },
      },
    },
  };
  return await Realm.open(config);
}

async function run() {
  const realm = await connect();

  console.log(`>>> Connected: ${realm.syncSession.isConnected()}`);
  // If I write a document to my collection here, it gets synced to Atlas

  // wait 10 seconds
  await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 10000));  
  console.log(`>>> Connected: ${realm.syncSession.isConnected()}`);
  // If I write a document  here, it does not appear in Atlas. It appears the next time I run the script though.
}

run().catch(err => console.error(`${err}`));

I do not get any errors (neither in the code, nor in the realm logs), but the second console.log says Connected: false. If I write to the database, it always writes to the local realm. But anything that is written after a few seconds of connection does not get synced (gets synced the next time I run my code). What am I doing wrong here?

embedfield:
filtering pymongo list_collection_names throws type error

Why should the following code throw TypeError: 'dict' object is not callable?

myclient = pymongo.MongoClient('x.x.x.x', username='xxxxxx', 
            password='yyyyyyy', authSource='zzzz', authMechanism='SCRAM-SHA-256')
mydb = myclient["db"]    
filter = {"name": {"$regex": r"^(?!system\.)"}}
collection = mydb.list_collection_names(filter=filter)
collection.sort()
filtered_names = list(filter(lambda x: "test" in x, collection ))

It is pymongo 4.4.1
answer: Thank you so much for your help. It is working like a charm. This is exactly what i was looking for.:-
